Message.Title: Current levels are crucial
Message.Msg: The $870-880 levels are being tested. If they do not hold, then $840 could be the next stop. The fall from $920 has not been with exceptional volumes so there is no huge momentum at the moment. It seems like a phase of profit booking which may continue till the range is clearly established. Possibility of a broad range of $840 to $920 is pretty high. This is because $920 is a price which has a lot of future positives factored and going below $840 may take some huge negative news flow. Meanwhile news regarding the lawsuits continued, with the EU not being totally satisfied with Google's response to the anti-trust issues. Mainly, it is being accused of using its dominant position as a search engine to manipulate search results to its advantage. It is alleged that the search results are not totally based on relevance, and favors its own services like YouTube. This has allegedly hurt the local businesses as the practice is anti-competitive. Though legally there may be a point in this, often these lawsuits seem to presume that Google is supposed to be providing a community service of sorts rather than running a business. In any case, these lawsuits are not going to go away and Google has to live with them. There are also the patent infringement lawsuits like the one against Vringo (VRNG). These lawsuits are on the rise all the time with this becoming a business model for companies. Spherix Inc (SPEX) which was into building an IPR portfolio around drug research recently became a full service IP company to leverage the growth in the IP monetizing business. For Google, these cases take the focus away from the good things it may be doing on the innovation front.
